## 🚨 Problem Statement

Independent gas station and car wash operators are being outcompeted by national chains with robust digital ecosystems. They lack the tools to build recurring revenue, prevent fraud, and drive in-store traffic.

### Owner Pain Points

| Pain Point | Impact |
|---|---|
| No integrated digital membership system | Manual workflows, high admin cost |
| Membership fraud via barcode sharing | ~15–20% revenue leakage |
| Thin gas margins (~$0.03–0.05/gal net) | Unsustainable as standalone revenue |
| No in-store traffic conversion tools | Missed high-margin convenience revenue |
| No access to modern loyalty tech | Can't compete with chains like Sheetz, Wawa |

### Customer Pain Points

| Pain Point | Impact |
|---|---|
| Tedious sign-up / renewal flows | Low conversion, high drop-off |
| Physical cards easy to lose | Churn trigger |
| No centralized benefits view | Low perceived value |
| Generic, untargeted promotions | Low redemption rates |

