## 🔍 Research & Discovery

### 1️⃣ User Interviews

| Participant Group | Count |
|---|---|
| Independent gas station owners | 12 |
| Car wash operators | 6 |
| Frequent customers (3+ visits/month) | 25 |
| **Total** | **43** |

### 2️⃣ Key Findings

```
83% of owners want predictable monthly recurring revenue
71% report active membership misuse or barcode sharing
68% say fuel profits alone are unsustainable long-term
76% want better tools to convert fuel visits → in-store purchases
92% of customers prefer mobile-first loyalty over physical cards
```

### 3️⃣ Competitive Analysis

| Capability | National Chains (Sheetz, Wawa, Circle K) | Independent Operators (Today) | FuelFlow (Target State) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Mobile membership management | ✅ Full | ❌ None | ✅ Full |
| Secure anti-fraud barcode | ✅ Yes | ❌ No | ✅ Dynamic refresh |
| Fuel discount engine | ✅ Yes | ⚠️ Manual | ✅ Automated |
| In-store promotions | ✅ Personalized | ❌ Paper coupons | ✅ Push + digital |
| Owner dashboard | ✅ Enterprise | ❌ None | ✅ SaaS lite |
| Setup complexity | 🔴 High (custom build) | — | 🟢 Plug-and-play |
| Cost | 🔴 $500K+ build | — | 🟢 SaaS pricing |

### 4️⃣ Market Insight

- **150,000+** independent gas stations in the US (NACS 2023)
- Convenience retail margins: **25–35%** gross vs fuel's **2–5%**
- Subscription economy CAGR: **~18%** (2023–2028)
- Mobile loyalty programs increase visit frequency by **~30%** on average

