## 🚀 Launch Strategy

### Pilot Design

```
Phase 1: 3 stations (Month 1–3)
├── 1× high-volume urban station
├── 1× suburban combo (gas + car wash)
└── 1× rural independent (lower traffic baseline)

Goal: Validate unit economics across station types
```

### Go-To-Market Channels

| Channel | Tactic | Cost | Expected Reach |
|---|---|---|---|
| In-store QR signage | Pump toppers + receipt QR | $200/station | 100% of foot traffic |
| Member referral | $5 credit for referred member | ~$5/acquisition | 20% of signups |
| Local digital ads | Geo-targeted Facebook/IG | $300/mo/station | 5-mile radius |
| Owner network | NACS/PEI conference outreach | $0 (organic) | Industry word-of-mouth |
| Email drip | Post-signup onboarding (5 emails) | $0 (Mailchimp free) | 100% of signups |

### Onboarding Flow

```
Customer Journey:
  See pump QR → Scan → Landing page → Sign up (2 min)
  → Enter payment → Barcode issued → Immediate wash access

Owner Journey:
  Sales demo → 30-min setup call → Dashboard training
  → Go live → Weekly check-in (Month 1)
```

